\f1\i0 \'a0Just as \'a7 6(a) does not suggest that this more protective standard need not meet the definition of a national consensus standard set forth in \'a7 3(9), so \'a7 6(b)(5) does not suggest that the most protective toxic material standard need not conform to the definition of a "standard" in \'a7 3(8).\
