\f1\b0\fs32 \cf0 \strokec3 Congress enacted the Occupational Safety and Health Act as a response to what was characterized as "the grim history of our failure to heed the occupational health needs of our workers." [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/448/607/#F4/1"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 Footnote 4/1}}] The failure of voluntary action and legislation at the state level,\'a0
